cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a new architecture for fully convolutional networks for semantic segmentation, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed architecture introduces competition amongst layers, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) to improve performance. The paper also mentions the use of specialized sub-networks, which is a concept commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM).
